   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">C</seg>Hristian Rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>der, Drinke heere of the waters of the heauēly Ci<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sterne, ouer-flow<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ing with the water of life, smell of the pleasāt fruit of the tree of life, placed in Paradise; and
<pb facs="11"/> taste thereby how good the Lord is: gather heere the pleasaunt flowers, and reap, if not the haruest, yet the gleanings of com<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fort: with iudge<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ment &amp; humility, learne wisedome of the spirit of true
<pb facs="11"/> wisedome: and suf<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fer thy eyes to be<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>hold the beames of cōsolatiō, life, light, and loue, procee<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ding from that e<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ternall Sun of safe<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tie, the onely belo<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ued of God, the true light and life of the world, and longed-for
<pb facs="12"/> ioye of men. And for al be thāk<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ful to him to whom al praise belōgeth. So, the Lord giue thee vnderstāding in all things. Fare<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>well,</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>In Christ. <hi>W. G.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
